      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-29T19:05:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this one should stay here. It\u0027s depending on a somewhere-else //third_party/zlib:zlib in Chromium, but it has the Crashpad-required-job of setting CRASHPAD_ZLIB_SOURCE_SYSTEM, CRASHPAD_ZLIB_SOURCE_CHROMIUM, or CRASHPAD_ZLIB_SOURCE_EMBEDDED (to support system zlib on Mac, or embedded zlib for Windows, unrelated to Chromium support).\n\n[If Crashpad switched to GN for standalone builds, it\u0027d probably just be easiest to always use embedded zlib, store it in //third_party/zlib in the Crashpad tree (without the second level sub dir) and be done with it, unless there\u0027s a strong reason to use the system one.]",
      "parentUuid": "ebcf9f04_9121c20f",
      "revId": "7180c656ba370aab6d316778b158d8660aeae768",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
